11
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:45,536
Uncle Dave said it...

12
00:01:45,604 --> 00:01:47,003
"Daylight is a dream

13
00:01:47,072 --> 00:01:49,666
if you live with your eyes closed."

14
00:01:49,742 --> 00:01:52,711
Well, my eyes are open now.
I see the choir.

15
00:01:52,778 --> 00:01:54,837
I know they're dressed in rags,

16
00:01:54,914 --> 00:01:57,075
but we're part of that choir.

17
00:01:57,149 --> 00:01:58,514
Yeah, both of us,

18
00:01:58,584 --> 00:02:00,848
and you, Maury, and Uncle Dave.

19
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,319
Sun's comin' up, kid.

20
00:02:02,388 --> 00:02:04,117
They'll be hawkin' the fish

21
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,623
down on Fulton Street.

22
00:02:05,691 --> 00:02:07,124
Let 'em hawk.

23
00:02:07,193 --> 00:02:09,286
Let 'em sing their hearts out.

24
00:02:09,361 --> 00:02:10,623
That's it, kid.

25
00:02:10,696 --> 00:02:13,130
Take that ruined choir.
Make it sing.

26
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,564
So long, Maury.

27
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,100
So long.

28
