[Mosquito Buzzes]

199
00:13:44,589 --> 00:13:46,523
Is that him?

200
00:13:46,591 --> 00:13:49,856
Is that Barton Fink?

201
00:13:49,927 --> 00:13:51,326
Let me at him.

202
00:13:51,396 --> 00:13:54,024
Let me put my arms
around this guy.

203
00:13:54,098 --> 00:13:56,032
Let me hug this guy.

204
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:58,068
How the hell are ya?

205
00:13:58,136 --> 00:13:59,160
Good trip?

206
00:13:59,237 --> 00:14:00,704
My name's Jack Lipnick.

207
00:14:00,772 --> 00:14:02,637
You know that.
You read the papers.

208
00:14:02,707 --> 00:14:04,436
Lou treating you all right?

209
00:14:04,509 --> 00:14:06,739
What's the matter
with your face?

210
00:14:06,811 --> 00:14:09,143
What's the matter
with his face, Lou?

211
00:14:09,213 --> 00:14:10,612
It's not so bad.

212
00:14:10,682 --> 00:14:12,673
A mosquito in my room.

213
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,978
Where'd we put him?

214
00:14:14,052 --> 00:14:15,451
I'm at the Earle.

215
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,954
Never heard of it.
Let's move him.

216
00:14:18,022 --> 00:14:19,284
Stay at my place.

217
00:14:19,357 --> 00:14:20,949
I wanted a place a little less...

218
00:14:21,025 --> 00:14:23,516
Less Hollywood. Say it.
It's not a dirty word.

219
00:14:23,594 --> 00:14:25,653
Say whatever you want.

220
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:28,290
The writer is king
at Capitol Pictures.

221
00:14:28,366 --> 00:14:29,628
Look at your paycheck.

222
00:14:29,701 --> 00:14:31,794
That's what
we think of writers.

223
00:14:31,869 --> 00:14:34,804
So, what kind of pictures
does he like?

224
00:14:34,872 --> 00:14:37,500
Mr. Fink hasn't given
a preference, Mr. Lipnick.

225
00:14:37,575 --> 00:14:39,668
So, how about it, Bart?

226
00:14:39,744 --> 00:14:41,678
Well, uh, to be honest,

227
00:14:41,746 --> 00:14:44,476
I don't go to the pictures much.

228
00:14:44,549 --> 00:14:45,573
That's okay.

229
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:47,345
You probably
walked in here

230
00:14:47,418 --> 00:14:49,978
thinking that was going
to be a handicap,

231
00:14:50,054 --> 00:14:52,989
thinking we wanted people
who knew something about the medium,

232
00:14:53,057 --> 00:14:55,525
thinking there's technical
mumbo jumbo to learn.

233
00:14:55,593 --> 00:14:57,151
You were dead wrong.

234
00:14:57,228 --> 00:15:00,425
There's only one thing...
Can you tell a story?

235
00:15:00,498 --> 00:15:02,728
Can you make us laugh,
make us cry,

236
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,360
make us want
to break out in song?

237
00:15:05,436 --> 00:15:06,835
That more than one thing?

238
00:15:06,904 --> 00:15:09,906
I run this dump, and I don't know
technical mumbo jumbo.

239
00:15:10,039 --> 00:15:11,597
Why do I run it?

240
00:15:11,674 --> 00:15:14,108
'Cause I got horse sense, showmanship!

241
00:15:14,176 --> 00:15:16,940
And also I'm bigger
and meaner and louder

242
00:15:17,013 --> 00:15:19,379
than any other kike
in this town.

243
00:15:19,448 --> 00:15:21,939
I don't mean my dick's
bigger than yours.

244
00:15:22,018 --> 00:15:24,418
It's not a sexual thing.
Coffee?

245
00:15:27,023 --> 00:15:28,490
Yes, thank you.

246
00:15:28,557 --> 00:15:29,524
Lou!

247
00:15:37,033 --> 00:15:39,934
Used to have shares
in the company,

248
00:15:40,002 --> 00:15:41,094
ownership interest,

249
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:43,730
got bought out...
muscled out.

250
00:15:43,806 --> 00:15:46,741
We keep him around.
He's got a family.

251
00:15:46,809 --> 00:15:48,140
Poor schmuck.
He's sensitive.

252
00:15:48,210 --> 00:15:50,474
Don't mention the old days.
Hell, say whatever you want.

253
00:15:50,546 --> 00:15:51,979
Look, barring a preference,

254
00:15:52,048 --> 00:15:54,983
you'll be working on
a wrestling picture... Wallace Beery.

255
00:15:55,051 --> 00:15:58,020
They say you know
the poetry of the street.

256
00:15:58,087 --> 00:15:59,918
That rules out
westerns, pirates,

257
00:15:59,989 --> 00:16:01,854
screwball, Bible, Roman...

258
00:16:01,924 --> 00:16:04,415
I'm not some guy
that thinks poetic is fruity.

259
00:16:04,493 --> 00:16:05,926
We're together on that.

260
00:16:05,995 --> 00:16:07,929
I'm from New York myself.

261
00:16:07,997 --> 00:16:10,966
Minsk... if you want
to go all the way back,

262
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:13,627
which we won't
if you don't mind.

263
00:16:13,703 --> 00:16:15,432
People will say to you...

264
00:16:15,504 --> 00:16:18,132
Wallace Beery, wrestling...
it's a B picture.

265
00:16:18,207 --> 00:16:19,606
You tell them... bullshit!

266
00:16:19,675 --> 00:16:22,838
We don't make B pictures
here at Capitol.

267
00:16:22,912 --> 00:16:26,245
Let's put a stop
to that rumor right now.

268
00:16:26,315 --> 00:16:28,442
